AHEAD of headies’s next rated award, singer and songwriter Zinoleesky has put his hope in God. In an exclusive chat with The Nation, the music star who is nominated in the ‘next rated awards’ category alongside Ayra Starr, BNXN, Lojay, and Ruger, says it’s God for him.   Nigerian singer Akinwande features British actress Naomi…     Summer money greater than summer body – DJ Cuppy     Why I must date a wealthy man, by Tiwa Savage   In his words, “I put God first, and like I said any nomination in any award is showing that at least people recognize you and that’s what’s up so God all the way still.” Since his breakout with Kilofeshe, the Marlian Music signee has kept churning out hit songs that include Ma Pariwo, Naira Marley, Gone far, Rocking, and Loving. He has also worked on different collaborations with several music acts that include Lil Kesh on Don’t call me, BNXN on Kilometre remix, and Naira Marley on O dun. The 2022 edition of the Headies Awards is scheduled to hold on Sunday, September 4, 2022, at the COBB Energy Performing Arts Center in Atlanta, USA.